      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "usp_Published_GetAccountInformationByAgencyCode",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to retrieve account information from a billing system based on either an agency code or a facility number. It logs the usage of the report, determines whether to filter results by agency or facility, and then queries the database to return detailed account and facility information."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Medium"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The procedure involves multiple steps, including logging, conditional logic to determine query paths, and a complex SQL query with multiple joins. The use of a temporary table and dynamic filtering adds to its complexity."
        }
      ]
    },
